# StartOS File Models

Settings persist to `/mostro/settings.toml` via `daemon_settings` in `settings.ts`.

## Schema rules

```typescript
import { FileHelper, z } from '@start9labs/start-sdk'

const natural = (defaultVal: number) =>
  z.number().int().nonnegative().catch(defaultVal)

// Every key needs .catch() — schema IS the default
fee: z.number().catch(0),
relays: z.array(z.string()).catch(['wss://relay.mostro.network']),

// Nested sections — resilient empty parse
mostro: mostroSchema.catch(() => mostroSchema.parse({})),
```

## Path API (SDK 1.5)

```typescript
FileHelper.toml({ base: sdk.volumes.main, subpath: './settings.toml' }, shape)
```

## Read / write

```typescript
// ✅ prefill (actions)
await daemon_settings.read((s) => s?.mostro).once()

// ✅ reactive (main.ts)
await daemon_settings.read((s) => s?.rpc?.enabled).const(effects)

// ✅ save
await daemon_settings.merge(effects, { mostro: { fee: input.fee } })

// ❌ never
await daemon_settings.write(...)
await daemon_settings.read((s) => s)  // identity read
```

When adding a field, also update `settings.tpl.toml` under the matching `[section]`.
